  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering at national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Frameworks\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting (SAR) protocols\n\n3. Key Strategies\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- Imposing significant penalties for non-compliance\n- International cooperation between financial institutions\n\n4. Regulatory Bodies\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Central banks\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Financial regulators\n\n5. Compliance Mechanisms\n- Risk assessment procedures\n- Regular audits\n- Staff training programs\n- Advanced technological screening systems\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities across different jurisdictions and financial sectors.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering legal frameworks?",
